The African Action Congress (AAC) has said that its National Working Committee (NWC) has concluded steps to submit the party’s membership register to the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). According to a statement issued by its National Publicly Secretary, Comrade Femi Adeyeye, on Tuesday, the action was in line with the requirements of the new Electoral Act 2022. The statement read, “We urge all members, prospectives and aspirants for the 2023 elections, who are yet to register on the party’s website to do so before 12 noon on Wednesday, May 4, 2022. -Advertisement- “Failure to register could amount to some sort of disenfranchisement, even as it concerns party primaries. “Please visit aacparty.org/volunteer to register now.”